//Topic
Real time chat application made using MERN stack 


//What was used ?
 Html , Javascript , Css. 
  

ALL BELOW ARE JAVASCRIPT IN DIFFERENT SKINS. 
This is the stack that used to make website.
Stack is the combination of different tools  (For example : 'MERN' stack)

M -> Mongo database : Used to store user data like username password and messages.

E -> Express js : Used for making simple server. Server is the middleman between frontend and backend server gets data from database and displays on frontend/browser. Also it sends data feom frontend to backend.

R -> React js : React js is a framework for javascript. In simple words it is javascript. used to make the frontend. and connect it to the server.

N -> Node js : used for server. Express js uses Node to make sever easily 



//What was made? 

Backend also known as Server  -- Server , Database and whatever else the user will not see sits in the backend. Think of it as a backstage of a show.

Frontend also known as Client   -- Frontend is everything that a user will see. Page, button, dashboard. This is the show. User will interact with  this.

These 2 are separatedly made and later connected. Server usually made before backend


//Why is socket used? 
Used Socket.io a free service on internet to make the realtime connection possible. If this was not used we would have had to reload the page all the time to see if any message was sent or received. 


//Working of the web app .

first is the landing page, Click on "get started" to go to the login/register page.
On Register page user can make an account and then log in into the application.
after loggin in, chat dashboard opens where the user can chat with the other loggedin user. 


//How does login work? 

When user enters username and password in frontend it goes to the backend to server and then server send it to database to check if any username matches with the stored username and if it does it will check for the password if it matches the user is logged in else a alert is shown denying access




